<ed:glossary xmlns:text="http://www.openfuxml.org/text" xmlns:ofx="http://www.openfuxml.org" xmlns:layout="http://www.openfuxml.org/layout" xmlns:media="http://www.openfuxml.org/media" xmlns:ed="http://www.openfuxml.org/editorial" xmlns:wiki="http://www.openfuxml.org/wiki" xmlns:l="http://www.openfuxml.org/list" xmlns:table="http://www.openfuxml.org/table">
    <ed:term code="Latitude">
    	<text:text classifier="name">Latitude and Longitude</text:text>
        <text:text classifier="text">latitude and longitude</text:text>
        <ofx:paragraph lang="en">
            The system WGS 84 in decimal notation has to be used. The World Geodetic System (WGS) is a standard in cartography, geodesy and navigation.
            It comprises a standard coordinate system for the earth, a standard spheroidal reference surface (th datum or reference ellipsoid) for raw altitude data and a gravitational equipotential surface (the geoid) the defines the nominal sea level.
        </ofx:paragraph>
        <ofx:paragraph lang="fr">
            latitude and longitude FR
        </ofx:paragraph>
    </ed:term>
    <ed:term code="geospatial">
        <text:text classifier="name">Geospatial</text:text>
        <text:text classifier="text">geospatial</text:text>
        <ofx:paragraph lang="en">
            Of or pertaining to a geographic location, especially data.
        </ofx:paragraph>
        <ofx:paragraph lang="fr">
            geospatial FR
        </ofx:paragraph>
    </ed:term>
</ed:glossary>